lobe","Temporal lobe","Occipital lobe","Parietal lobe","Limbic system"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eparietal lobe\u003C/strong\u003E contains the primary somatosensory cortex in the postcentral gyrus, which is responsible for processing sensory information including touch, temperature, pressure, and pain. Lesions here typically cause deficits in sensation and spatial awareness.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Efrontal lobe\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily involved in motor function, executive planning, and personality. The \u003Cstrong\u003Etemporal lobe\u003C/strong\u003E processes auditory information and plays a role in memory formation. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eoccipital lobe\u003C/strong\u003E processes visual information. The \u003Cstrong\u003Elimbic system\u003C/strong\u003E is involved in emotion, memory, and behaviour.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAstereognosis (inability to recognise objects by touch) and impaired two-point discrimination are classic signs of parietal lobe dysfunction, particularly affecting the primary somatosensory cortex.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The primary somatosensory cortex is located in the postcentral gyrus of the parietal lobe.","The parietal lobe processes sensory information including touch, temperature, pressure, and pain.","Lesions in the parietal lobe can cause sensory deficits, astereognosis, and problems with spatial awareness."],"references":["Souza-Couto D, Bretas R, Aversi-Ferreira TA. Neuropsychology of the parietal lobe: Luria\u0027s and contemporary conceptions. Front Neurosci. 2023 Oct 20;17:1226226. doi: 10.3389/fnins.2023.1226226. PMID: 37928730; PMCID: PMC10623013.","Purves D, Augustine GJ, Fitzpatrick D, et al., editors. Neuroscience. 2nd edition. Sunderland (MA): Sinauer Associates; 2001. Lesions of the Parietal Association Cortex: Deficits of Attention. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK10998/","Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022).\u00a0The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50578"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16384"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50578","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50578"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-25T15:42:31+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-25T15:43:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9075"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65142"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","s